    "Id": "vehiclechassisdef_PO",
    "Name": "Po",
    "Details": "<b>Name: <color=#85DBF6>Po Heavy Tank</color>\nArmor: <color=#85DBF6>Standard </color>\tTechnology: <color=#85DBF6>Inner Sphere</color>\nMovement: <color=#85DBF6>4/6 (Tracked)</color>\tEngine: <color=#85DBF6>240 ICE</color></b>\n\nThe Po Heavy Tank is a simple and reliable combat vehicle, often derided as a poor man's Patton/Rommel tank. It is named after the mischievous and vengeful spirit of Chinese tradition, and has become the principal combat vehicle on Capellan worlds lacking BattleMech units.\n\nThe tank carries an uninspired but serviceable weapon array, with the main offensive punch coming from a turret-mounted AC/10. This makes the Po a serious combat threat to light and medium 'Mechs. Two machine guns, one mounted next to the autocannon and the other mounted in a ball joint on the front of the tank, serve as secondary weapons.",
